ctive of inner realms is explored—through a hospital stay, a sudden name change, or the surprising end of all those dreaded piano lessons.Taken together, these stories are a far greater whole than the sum of their remarkable parts, an unfor­gettable exploration of the paradoxical toughness and vulnerability that define the mortal condition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aFiction. 4aLiterature. 4aNew York City & Regional. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aO'Donnell, Angela Alaimo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Donnell, Angela Alaimo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311075168040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781531507497?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781531507497423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781531507497/original  a978-3-11-075168-0  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles